element.name: Cork Boot by Besiebob, Traditional Cache (1/1.5)
element.description: This cache is a small container, wrapped in black, up high but within arms reach. A short, easy walk, with a bit of an incline for the last few feet.
element.encoded-hints: In the fork of an ivy covered tree.

ul.li:
2010-03-22T19:00:00Z : Found it by Lauris_79
Need some time to find, but was ok.

2010-02-23T20:00:00Z : Found it by Blue Jay 59
Found it while out with Toffee Man. Could do with a little TLC TFTC Blue Jay 59 #209

2010-02-23T20:00:00Z : Found it by Toffee Man
Found this cache lying on the ground with no black bag covering it. We rehid the cache low down where it would not be so easily spotted. Log very damp & could do with some maintainance. TFTC Toffee Man #209

2010-02-21T20:00:00Z : Didn't find it by Frezeluberz
Couldn't find it. Didn't really spend a lot of time looking. Think we found where it should have been. Didn't investigate the ground.

2009-07-19T19:00:00Z : Found it by Kersti.com
Out for a day of caching with JME1979 - this was our third find for the day and my 300th overall. The heavens opened up as we were approaching 200m from the cache, by the time it was in hand we were drenched and trying unsuccessfully to get cover from the trees. Figuring that we were as wet as we could possibly get anyway we headed back to the car - and naturally it dried up as we got back.
